Water fasting is a more extended and restrictive form of fasting where only water is consumed for a specified period, ranging from 24 hours to several days or even weeks. This method requires careful planning and should be undertaken with medical supervision, especially for longer durations.

Intermittent fasting involves cycling between periods of eating and fasting. There are several popular methods within intermittent fasting, such as the 16/8 method, which involves a daily fast for 16 hours and an eating window of 8 hours.
